<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>User Guide - Remote Control Car</title>
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
<style>
  /* Extra styles specific to the Guide page */
  .guide-container {
    max-width: 800px;
    width: 100%;
    padding: 20px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 20px;
  }

  .guide-title {
    text-align: center;
    color: #4CAF50;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    font-size: 2rem;
  }

  .guide-card {
    background: #222;
    border: 1px solid #333;
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 20px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
  }

  .guide-card h3 {
    color: #2196F3;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #444;
    padding-bottom: 5px;
  }

  .guide-card ul {
    list-style-type: none;
    padding-left: 5px;
  }

  .guide-card li {
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .key-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    background: #444;
    color: #fff;
    padding: 2px 8px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-family: monospace;
    border: 1px solid #666;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .btn-example {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 2px 8px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: white;
    vertical-align: middle;
  }
  
  .back-link {
    display: block;
    width: fit-content;
    margin: 20px auto 0;
    color: #aaa;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    padding: 10px 20px;
    border: 1px solid #444;
    border-radius: 6px;
    transition: 0.3s;
  }
  
  .back-link:hover {
    background: #333;
    color: #fff;
    border-color: #fff;
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
  <h2>Remote Control Car</h2>
  <div class="status-bar">
    <span>üìñ User Guide</span>
  </div>
</header>

<main>
  <div class="guide-container">
    <h1 class="guide-title">How to Use</h1>

    <div class="guide-card">
      <h3>1. Driving Controls</h3>
      <p>You can control the car using either the on-screen buttons or your keyboard.</p>
      <br>
      <ul>
        <li><span class="key-badge">W</span> or <span class="key-badge">‚Üë</span> : Move Forward</li>
        <li><span class="key-badge">S</span> or <span class="key-badge">‚Üì</span> : Move Backward</li>
        <li><span class="key-badge">A</span> or <span class="key-badge">‚Üê</span> : Turn Left</li>
        <li><span class="key-badge">D</span> or <span class="key-badge">‚Üí</span> : Turn Right</li>
        <li><em>Combine keys (e.g., W+A) to move diagonally.</em></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="guide-card">
      <h3>2. Camera & Capture</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Take a Photo:</strong> Press the <span class="key-badge">C</span> key on your keyboard OR click the <span class="btn-example" style="background:#2196F3">Capture (C)</span> button.
        </li>
        <li>
          The captured image will automatically be saved to the server and appear in the image gallery (instructed below).
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="guide-card">
      <h3>3. Gallery & AI Analysis</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>View Gallery:</strong> Click the <span class="btn-example" style="background:#9C27B0">üìÅ Gallery</span> button to open the image drawer.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Inspect Image:</strong> Click on any thumbnail in the gallery to view it full-screen.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Analyze Image:</strong> While viewing an image full-screen, click the <span class="btn-example" style="background:#ff9800">üîç Analyze Image</span> button. The AI will scan the photo and list detected objects (e.g., "Car: 98%").
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    
    <a href="/" class="back-link">‚Üê Back to Home</a>
  </div>
</main>

</body>
</html>